{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"88699d73-082f-4840-bcbd-fc44bfe934b8","content":"The problem is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, file order matters — files can only use types from files listed **above** them. `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but it depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFixing by moving `Domain.fs` before `Services.fs`:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_VL95EARIUWX5E6BUoFpSnq","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-20d6e5bc21874c96a5cd591a17bd1316/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-20d6e5bc21874c96a5cd591a17bd1316/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"e13460b5-e1f2-4a41-8520-8352ec0dbab9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed before them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. `Services.fs` — depends on `Domain.fs` (uses `Order` type)\n2. `Domain.fs` — defines the `Order` type\n3. `Program.fs` — depends on both\n\n`Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, which hasn't been compiled yet. The fix is to reorder so `Domain.fs` comes first.","outputTokens":402,"requestId":"5C1D:3A7531:5E785EF:6746008:69F15601"},"id":"57585395-c626-498c-a002-0c4ca484825a","timestamp":"2026-04-29T00:51:22.687Z","parentId":"fb710bee-0c20-4ce9-a5d5-906c74bce736"}
